As the bulk Rashba effect must arise from a net sum of site asymmetries (that is local inversion symmetry breaking)4, the controversy over the presence of Rashba splitting in perovskites has focused on the source of inversion symmetry breaking. The general consensus is that these materials crystallize in inversion symmetric phases at all temperatures. In our case, we have observed a correlation between the observation of the signature of Rashba splitting in the TP-PLE spectrum and a spectrally dependent TP-PL pump intensity dependence. Namely, the intensity dependence exponent, γ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
